\begin{center}
{\Large Speaker Evaluation}
\end{center}

\begin{flushleft}

Speaker's Name:

\vspace{4mm}
Your Name: 

\end{flushleft}
Please respond briefly to the following questions.  Please hand these forms
directly to the speaker when you are done.  The speaker is the only person
besides yourself who will see your response.


\begin{itemize}

\item {\bf Use of overheads}
	\begin{enumerate}
		\item Were the overheads readable?

		\vspace{5mm}

		\item Was there too much/not enough/just the right amount of
		information per overhead?

		\vspace{5mm}
	\end{enumerate}


\item {\bf Speaking Mechanics }

	\begin{enumerate}
		\item  Did the speaker mumble?  Talk too fast?  Too
		quietly?

		\vspace{5mm}

		\item  Did the speaker make sufficient eye contact with 
		the audience?

		\vspace{5mm}
	\end{enumerate}

\item {\bf Overall }

	\begin{enumerate}
		\item Did you find this talk generally understandable?  Did
		you leave this talk with a rough sense of what the speaker
		was talking about?  
		
		\vspace{5mm}

		\item What were this talk's strong points?

		\vspace{5mm}

		\item What could the speaker have done differently that would
		have made this talk better?

		\vspace{10mm}
	\end{enumerate}


\end{itemize}

Please feel free to add additional comments on the back.

